The paper deals with approximation algorithms for optimization problems in metric spaces, specifically for problems related to vehicle routing and center/median problems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.RO (robotics), and cs.IT (information theory). However, given the focus on graph embeddings and approximation schemes, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are less likely but still possible, as they may be relevant to specific applications of the algorithms presented in the paper.
